definitions.definition: A member of the Syilx people.
A Salish language which arose among the indigenous peoples of the southern Interior Plateau region based primarily in the Okanagan River Basin and the Columbia River Basin.

main_definition: A member of the Syilx people.
secondary_definitions: ( linguistics , uncountable ) A Salish language which arose among the indigenous peoples of the southern Interior Plateau region based primarily in the Okanagan River Basin and the Columbia River Basin.
